Titolo: Caper in the Castro

Anno: 1989

Descrizione: Caper in the Castro is a murder mystery video game developed by C.M. Ralph and released in 1989. It is the earliest known computer game to focus on LGBT themes. The game was originally released for Mac computers and distributed freely on bulletin board systems as charityware to raise money for the AIDS epidemic.

Genere: Point-and-click adventure

Valutazione: N/A
